The paper deals with processing large semantic graph data, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB). The proposed approach involves identifying instance similarities and discovering type classes automatically, which are tasks commonly associated with machine learning (cs.AI) and data mining (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of locality-sensitive hashing, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and similarity search (cs.SI).
